{
  "stem": "512.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] a typhus broke out there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So the, the Nazis only told us, don't go to that-- close to there, because it's the contagious, it's a contagious disease.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And sometimes they would throw over a little bread [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] or a piece of clothing.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was-- Auschwitz was a miserable, miserable weather.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Either it was very hot that you would faint, or it was bitter cold.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And you know, we didn't-- we were not-- we didn't have, so we would hold on to each other and our bodies would-- one would warm the other.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So one day we heard screaming during the night.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] They burned down the whole camp because typhus had spread, so they burned it down.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And, and the food, the food in Auschwitz, it was, it was-- in the morning, it was that little soup that they gave us.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in the afternoon, again, it was the counting.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then after the counting, they would give us a piece of bread with margarine, with a piece of margarine, and that was-- those were the rations for the day.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were just biting that hard piece.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was like a brick, the size of a brick cut in, in four or six, whatever, and everybody had a, a slice of it.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Occasionally, men would come in to clean the, the toilets, and that's how they, we would send out messages and, sometimes, receive a message.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we would say, Bilky, do you know if there is any people from Bilky?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Next time I'll come, I'll ask.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So they, they would go and inquire and bring back a message, this one, and this one, you know, this one, and this one.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
